{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/dev/wsl-debian-setting/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"obtuseCave","author":"Han, Minhee","siteUrl":"https://han-minhee.github.io/blog","comment":{"disqusShortName":"","utterances":"han-minhee/blog"},"sponsor":{"buyMeACoffeeId":"esTfNE7"}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"912514ad-8777-5bc7-990e-b65c95357360","excerpt":"Prerequisite Windows 10 Version 16215.0 or higher (most Windows 10 machines meet this standard) Turn on Required Windows Features Turn on Developer Mode Go to windows settings and turn on Developer mode After hitting  key, or in  search for  Turn on  Reboot Turn on WSL In…","html":"<h3 id=\"prerequisite\"><a href=\"#prerequisite\" aria-label=\"prerequisite permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisite</h3>\n<p>Windows 10 Version 16215.0 or higher (most Windows 10 machines meet this standard)</p>\n<h3 id=\"turn-on-required-windows-features\"><a href=\"#turn-on-required-windows-features\" aria-label=\"turn on required windows features permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Turn on Required Windows Features</h3>\n<h4 id=\"turn-on-developer-mode\"><a href=\"#turn-on-developer-mode\" aria-label=\"turn on developer mode permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Turn on Developer Mode</h4>\n<p>Go to windows settings and turn on Developer mode</p>\n<ol>\n<li>After hitting <code class=\"language-text\">win</code> key, or in <code class=\"language-text\">settings</code> search for <code class=\"language-text\">Developer settings</code></li>\n<li>Turn on <code class=\"language-text\">Developer mode</code></li>\n<li>Reboot</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"turn-on-wsl\"><a href=\"#turn-on-wsl\" aria-label=\"turn on wsl permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Turn on WSL</h4>\n<p>In PowerShell, run:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"powershell\"><pre class=\"language-powershell\"><code class=\"language-powershell\">Enable<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>WindowsOptionalFeature <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>Online <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>FeatureName Microsoft<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>Windows<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>Subsystem<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>Linux</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"install-debian-in-microsoft-store\"><a href=\"#install-debian-in-microsoft-store\" aria-label=\"install debian in microsoft store permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install Debian in Microsoft Store</h3>\n<p>In Windows Store, search for “debian” and install <a href=\"https://www.microsoft.com/store/apps/9MSVKQC78PK6\">Debian</a>.\nWhy Debian? Acutally not much reasons. I’ve chosen Debain as it “feels”(I don’t have any concrete evidence) more stable for me. Then, run Debian from the start menu, follow the instructions.</p>\n<h3 id=\"upgrade-to-buster-debian-10\"><a href=\"#upgrade-to-buster-debian-10\" aria-label=\"upgrade to buster debian 10 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Upgrade to Buster (Debian 10)</h3>\n<p>In Debian shell, run</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">sed</span> -i <span class=\"token string\">'s/stretch/buster/g'</span> /etc/apt/sources.list</code></pre></div>\n<p>then</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt</span> update\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt</span> upgrade</code></pre></div>\n<p>Done.</p>\n<h3 id=\"change-mirror\"><a href=\"#change-mirror\" aria-label=\"change mirror permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Change mirror</h3>\n<p>As I’m currently in Korea, I changed the mirror to Korea.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">sed</span> -i <span class=\"token string\">'s/deb.debian/ftp.kr.debian/g'</span> /etc/apt/sources.list  </code></pre></div>\n<p>put desired mirror in <code class=\"language-text\">ftp.kr.debian</code>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"setup-x-window-gui-environment\"><a href=\"#setup-x-window-gui-environment\" aria-label=\"setup x window gui environment permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Setup X-Window Gui Environment</h3>\n<p>Now, to run GUI applications, we need to install Windows X-server.</p>\n<p>Install <a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/vcxsrv/\">VcXsrv</a> and run X-server. No additional settings required.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> systemd-machine-id-setup\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> dbus-uuidgen --ensure</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sed</span> -e <span class=\"token string\">\"\\<span class=\"token variable\">$aexport</span> DISPLAY=:0\"</span> ~/.bashrc\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">source</span> ~/.bashrc</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now, you are ready to run GUI apps for WSL.</p>\n<h3 id=\"setup-visual-studio-code-for-wsl\"><a href=\"#setup-visual-studio-code-for-wsl\" aria-label=\"setup visual studio code for wsl permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Setup Visual Studio Code for WSL</h3>\n<p>Install <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ms-vscode-remote.vscode-remote-extensionpack\">Remote Development extension pack</a> in VSCode, press <code class=\"language-text\">F1</code>(command shortcut) and search for <code class=\"language-text\">Remote-WSL: New Window</code> and run it.</p>\n<p>VSCode will install required files in WSL. In the remote WSL window, you can run and edit files in WSL. Done!</p>\n<h3 id=\"references\"><a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>References</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://askubuntu.com/questions/993225/whats-the-easiest-way-to-run-gui-apps-on-windows-subsystem-for-linux-as-of-2018\">What’s the easiest way to run GUI apps on Windows Subsystem for Linux as of 2018?</a>\n<a href=\"https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/20573/sed-insert-text-after-the-last-line\">SED: insert text after the last line?</a>\n<a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-gb/windows/wsl/install-win10\">Microsoft Docs</a>\n<a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/remote-overview\">VS Code Docs</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Setup Debian WSL on Windows","date":"July 13, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/dev/wsl-debian-setting/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/dev/coq-setup/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Install and setup opam/coq in debian / ubuntu","category":"devs"}},"next":null}}}